# Features Architecture

- Place new product logic under `src/features/<feature>/` with `types`, `services`, `hooks`, `components`.
- API routes must use `withApiHandler`, `jsonSuccess`, `jsonError`, and `requireAuthenticatedProfile` from `@/features/shared`.
- Social and matching routes live under `src/features/social` and `src/features/matching`.
- Questions and learning routes live under `src/features/questions` and `src/features/learning`.
- Role page guards: `features/shared/middleware/role-guards.ts` (wired in root `middleware.ts`).
- DB row Zod mirrors live in `src/features/shared/types/db-schemas.ts`; run `npm run db:schemas:check` after schema changes.
- Standard error body: `{ error: string, code: string }`.
- Do not duplicate domain logic: wrap `src/lib/domain/*` inside feature `services/`.
- Roles are `teacher`, `parent`, `student`. Institution is a registration account kind, not a middleware role.
- Auth stays on Supabase SSR + RLS; do not introduce NextAuth without an explicit migration plan.

See `docs/features-architecture.md` for module map and migration rules.
